                     <interp inst="t18120219-88-person781" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120219-88-person781" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Smith. On the 29th of January a gentleman brought a pair of stockings in, he enquired if they were Mr. Smith's property; I said, they were; on examining them I found they had been taken from the door. That gentleman is here, his name is Howard.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120219-88-person782">
                  EDWARD 
                  HOWARD
               <interp inst="t18120219-88-person782" type="surname" value="HOWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120219-88-person782" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18120219-88-person782" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was passing along Sun-street on the 27th of January about three o'clock I observed the prisoner with another suspicious character near Mr. Smith's door, the person that was with the prisoner snatched something when he came to the prisoner he gave it him, which the prisoner put under his jacket. I proceeded for about sixty yards, when I saw an opportunity I turned round and looked at the prisoner and the other man, they separated; I immediately crossed the street and seized the prisoner with the property in his possession, and with assistance I took the prisoner to Mr. Smith's house, where the stockings were stolen from. When I seized the prisoner he threw the stockings down, the person that assisted me picked them up.</p>
               <p>Q. Where they outside of the door - A. Close to the outside of the door.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18120219-88-person783">
                  THOMAS 
